Page Find:Dialog "The Find Dialog" {
    Header "The Find Dialog" BNF {Menu: Edit->Find, Key: ctrl-F} Para
	Text {Find searches through the } Link {display area.} MainWin:DisplayArea { for text.} Brk
	Indent {
		Text {First, there is the } Bold {Pattern} Text {. This is the text to be searched for.} Brk
		Text {Then there are the check boxes for Ignore Case and Regular Expression.} Brk
		Text {Then there are the radio buttons selecting search up or search down.} Brk
		Text {And finally, the buttons: Find Next and Cancel.} Para
		Text {By default, the search begins at the bottom of the } Link {display area.} MainWin:DisplayArea { and searches upwards for the next match.} Brk
		Text {By default, this is an ignore-case and non-regular-expression (i.e. normal) search.} Brk
	}
	Text {What about Regular Expressions?} Brk
	Indent {
		Text {That's a big question.} Brk
		Text {Regular expressions are a common *nix feature and are a standard part of Tcl.} Brk
		Text {They allow complex searches for text 'like' the Pattern.} Brk
		Text {If you want to understand more, search for "regular expressions" on the net.} Brk
		Text {I recommend it.} Brk
	}
}
