Page MainWin:DisplayArea "The World Display Area" {
    Header "The World Display Area"
	Text {The World Display Area shows the output from each world, one world
	  at a time, with styles applied to the text.  World buttons at the bottom
	  let you know which world is currently being displayed, the connection
	  status of each world, and which worlds have new text waiting to be
	  displayed.} Para
	Text {The world button with the black outline is the one currently being
	  displayed.} Para
	Text {The color of the light on a world button indicates whether that
	  world is connected (green), disconnected (red), or just now attempting
	  to connect (yellow).} Para
	Text {If a world has received new text that hasn't been displayed to the
	  user yet, then the light for that world will blink.  This can happen
	  in the currently displayed world if new text was recieved while the
	  user was reading scrollback, or if } Link {text paging} Prefs:Paging
	  Text { has stopped the display scrolling because a full screen of
	  text has been displayed since the last user input.} Para
}
Page MainWin:WorldButtons "The World Buttons" {
    Header "The World Buttons"
	Text {The World Buttons are a quick and convenient indicator of the status of connections, especially when multi-mucking (playing in several worlds at once.} Para
	Text {When connected to a world, a button will appear on the gray bar between the display area and the command area. This button has a small light, which is red, green or flashing:} Brk
	Indent {
