Page MainWin:CommandArea "The Command Entry Area" {
    Header "The Command Entry Area"
	Text {The Command Entry area is where the user types in commands to be
	  sent to the current world.  Local Trebuchet commands can also be entered
	  here.} Para
	Header {/commands}
	Text {If a command starts with a '/' character, then Trebuchet will assume
	  that it is either an internal TCL command, or it is a user entered }
	  Link "macro" Macros:Main Text {.} Para
	Text {If there is an internal TCL procedure that is named the same as
	  the first word of the line (including the '/'), then that TCL command
	  will be executed, with the rest of the line passed as arguments to it.
	  ie.:} Para
	Indent {
		Bold {/echo foo bar}
	}
	Text {...will run the TCL procedure /echo with the two arguments "foo" and
	  "bar".} Para
	Text {If there is no matching TCL procedure, then Trebuchet will look to
	  see if there is a macro with the given name (Not including the '/'
	  character.)  ie:} Para
	Indent {
		Bold {/foo bar baz}
	}
	Text {...will trigger the macro named foo, passing it "bar" and "baz" as
	  %1 and %2.  If there is neither a matching TCL procedure or
	  macro, then an error will be given.} Para
	Text {If you want to send a line to the given world that starts with a
	  '/' character, simply add a second '/' to the beginning of the line.
	  ie:} Para
	Indent {
		Bold {//foobar baz qux}
	}
	Text {...will strip the extra / of the beginning of the line, and send 
	  "} Bold {/foobar baz qux} Text {" to the current world without any
	  preparsing.} Para
	Header {\commands}
	Text {If a command starts with a '\' character, then Trebuchet will
	  attempt to execute any TCL code embedded in the line inside of []s,
	  and expand any variables starting with $, then it will send the results
	  to the current world.  This is useful in obscure situations, such as
	  telling someone the time, or what your Trebuchet settings are.  ie:} Para
	Indent {
        Bold {\say The time is: [clock format [clock seconds]]} Brk
        Bold {\pose 's Trebuchet version is: $treb_version} Brk
        Bold {\page revar=The macro is: [/macro:list foobar]} Brk
	}
	Text {Obviously, you want to be careful with this, so that you don't
	  quote your world passwords to someone.}
}
