Page Macros:Simple "Simple Macros" {
    Header "Simple Macros" BNF "A foot on the ladder." Para
    Text {In the simplest form, a macro will simply send a line of text to
	  the world that the player is currently connected to.  For example,
	  if the user typed:}
    Indent {
        Bold {/foo}
    }
    Text {Trebuchet might expand that macro, and send the text:}
    Indent {
        Bold {:dances around yelling,  "Foo!  Bar!"}
    }
    Text {...to the current world.  A macro might also expand into multiple
	      commands, for performing more than one action at a time.  This is
		  good for things like commands to take you to a specific place in
		  the current world.} Para
	Header "Creating a simple Macro"
	Indent {
		Bullet
		Text {Open the Macro Editor with the } Link {Option->Macros} Macros:Dialog Text { menu item.} Brk
